To handle errors in Pyton, you can use try-except blocks as follows:

```python
try:
    # code that may raise an error
except Exception as e:
    print("Error occurred:", e)
else:
    pass
```

In this example, the `except` block is used to catch any exceptions that might occur during execution of the code. The `pass` statement is used to skip the rest of the code and continue with the next line. This ensures that the program continues running even if an error occurs in one part
